itional costs for the copy. However effects based on any additional costs that were paid for the original spell are copied as though those same costs were paid for the copy too.£10/1/2009 : If a copy says that it affects “you” it affects the controller of the copy not the controller of the original spell. Similarly if a copy says that it affects an “opponent” it affects an opponent of the copy’s controller not an opponent of the original spell’s controller.','','Whenever a player casts an instant or sorcery spell each other player copies that spell. Each of those players may choose new targets for their copy.'),
